HEADWORD: Mnemosyne
<hw>Mne*mos"y*ne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>mnhmosy`nh</grk> remembrance, memory, and the goddess of memory.
See <er>Mnemonic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Class Myth.)</fld> <def>The goddess
of memory and the mother of the Muses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

